title: 820-01958 no power
message:
Arrived with water damage. After replacing affected components the board powers on to 20v at 0.12-0.14a

Strange, can hear a buzzing noise coming out of the board. Sounds like it either coming from the T2 chip or U7800

Tried DFU mode revive option which completed successfully but no changes.

What should be checked next??

title: 820-01958 no power
message:
So board turns on, but doesn't boot?
You may need to use restore option.
Ask the client if has data unsaved first.

title: 820-01958 no power
message:
Yes but no change after restore option.

When the board is on the bench if one of the screw holes to the left of CPU is just tapped with finger the buzzing noise goes away and the board jumps up to 0.24a for a few seconds. Once unplugged and plugged back in buzzing noise returns within a few seconds

title: 820-01958 no power
message:
Which voltages do you get on the board?
Do you note any drop on VCORE?

message: Looks like dead CPU. This board making same noise as the one in this video. [MEDIA=youtube]cI2EHxbqf4c[/MEDIA]

title: 820-01958 no power

Audio board was also affected by liquid?
T2 data lines close to PPBUS_G3H and liquid spill damage it easy.
I suppose T2 chip got bad and doesn't work properly.

title: 820-01958 no power

Yes, audio board had alot of liquid.

I assume you cant replace the T2 chips correct?
